main event: A red-orange, round object was observed pulsating and disappearing over the horizon near Tsu Shima, Japan.
interesting points: The object was described as red-orange in color and round in shape.
The object seemed to pulsate from deep red to light orange before disappearing over the horizon.
The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes by military personnel using visual observation and binoculars.
The object was tracked on radar and witnessed by several observers.
The reporting officer evaluated the object as likely being the planet Mars due to its location and behavior.
result: Likely identified as the planet Mars
photographs: No photographs present in the document
